headline: United Rentals (URI): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: United Rentals has followed the market’s trajectory closely, rising in tandem with the S&P 500 over the past six months. The stock has climbed by 12.2% to $802.84 per share while the index has gained 11.3%.
